==What do all those buttons do?==
From left to right:
:*[[File:en/Manual/Build rail.png]] '''Build Railways buttons''' (shortcut 1-4): [[en/Manual/Building tracks|Builds track]] in the selected direction, you can click and drag for non-diagonal tracks. It is more expensive to build track on farm land.
:*[[File:en/Manual/Build autorail.png]] '''[[en/Archive/Manual/Autorail]] button''': (shortcut A or 5) Click and drag, can also be used to build diagonal tracks (probably needs a better explanation->[[en/Archive/Manual/Autorail]]).
:*[[File:en/Manual/Clear title.png]] '''[[en/Manual/Landscaping|Clear land]] button''' (shortcut 6):Use the dynamite to clear squares of either your own track you've built wrong, or anything that's in your way. Don't demolish too many houses or buildings in a town because your company rating at that town will drop and they won't let you build any stations in their town.
:*[[File:en/Manual/Build traindepot.png]] '''Build [[en/Manual/Depots|depot]] button''' (shortcut 7): Opens the depot build window for you to select a depot direction to build. The Button will build a depot, for making and servicing vehicles. If you build a depot next to your own track, it will automatically build some track to connect it to your track. Take care to choose the depot facing the way you want it.
:*[[File:en/Manual/Build waypoint.png]] '''Build [[en/Manual/Waypoints|waypoint]] button''' (shortcut 8): Allows you to build a [[en/Manual/Waypoints]] on/over a rail track.
:*[[File:en/Manual/Build station.png]] '''Build [[en/Manual/Stations|station]] button''' (shortcut 9): Opens the station build window for you to select a station size and direction to build.
