==Types of Railway==
For these releases, electrified rail is added. This gives the following table:
:* [[en/Manual/Base Set/Railways]] - available from the beginning of the game. Both steam and diesel trains run on these railways, electric trains no longer do.
:* [[en/Manual/Base Set/Electrified railways]] - available when electric trains arrive (1965). Steam, diesel and electric trains run on these railways.
:* [[en/Manual/Base Set/Monorail]] - first available around 1999. Only trains built in a Monorail Depot will run on these rails.
:* [[en/Manual/Base Set/MagLev]] - the fastest of the four types of railway, first available around 2022

==Differences to [[en/Archive/OpenTTD/TTDPatch]]==
===0.5.0 and newer===
The monorails and maglevs are not merged and there are now electric railways (electric trains require them to run) unlike [[en/Archive/OpenTTD/TTDPatch]], where Monorail or Maglev can be sacrificed for a special electric track.

